detaileddescription.para: An issue arises however, because the model.ExpressionList still says to "short circuit" when the CloseParenthesisToken is encountered, and to at this point make the ParenthesizedExpressionNode the primary expression.
Well, the ParenthesizedExpressionNode should no longer exist, it was deemed to be more accurately described by a CommaSeparatedExpressionNode.
So, this method will remove any entries in the model.ExpressionList that have the 'ParenthesizedExpressionNode' as the to-be primary expression.
